On International Day of the Girl, President Joe Biden emphasizes the importance of empowering girls and ensuring they have the resources they need to thrive. He discusses the actions his administration has taken to advance gender equity and equality, including establishing the White House Gender Policy Council and releasing the first-ever United States National Strategy on Gender Equity and Equality. President Biden also highlights the investments made in education, mental health, and gun violence prevention to support the well-being of girls. He reaffirms the commitment to ending gender-based violence and promoting the rights of all women and girls, including transgender women and girls. Globally, the United States is doubling foreign assistance to promote gender equity and supporting access to healthcare and education for girls and young women. The proclamation concludes with a call to observe the International Day of the Girl with programs, ceremonies, and policies that advance equity and opportunity for girls everywhere.